<div id="infobox" class="infobox"> 
 <div class="table-responsive"> 
  <table class="wiki_table"> 
   <tbody> 
    <tr> 
     <th style="text-align: center;" colspan="2"> <h2>Roar Medallion</h2> </th> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td style="text-align: center;" colspan="2"><img style="width: 200px; height: 200px;" title="Roar Medallion" src="/file/Elden-Ring/roar_medallion_talisman_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png" alt="roar medallion talisman elden ring wiki guide 200px" width="200" height="200"></td> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td>Weight</td> 
     <td>0.7</td> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td colspan="2"><img title="item_effect_icon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_18px" src="/file/Elden-Ring/item_effects_icon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_55px_18px.png" alt="item effects icon elden ring wiki guide 55px 18px" width="18" height="18">Effect 
      <div class="lineleft"> 
       <img src="/file/Elden-Ring/status_effect_58_elden_ring_wiki_guide_44px.png" alt="status effect 58 elden ring wiki guide 44px" width="20" height="20">&nbsp;Increases the damage of roars and breath attacks by 15% 
      </div> </td> 
    </tr> 
   </tbody> 
  </table> 
 </div> 
</div> 
<p><strong>Roar Medallion</strong>&nbsp;is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Talismans" href="/Talismans">Talisman</a> in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>.&nbsp;Roar Medallion&nbsp;increases the damage of roars and breath attacks by 15%. Players can use talismans&nbsp;in Elden Ring to boost a variety of <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Stats" href="/Stats" target="">Stats</a>.</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>A bronze medallion depicting a roaring giant.<br>Enhances roars and breath attacks.</em></p> 
 <p><em>In ancient times, the giants were mortal enemies of the Erdtree. <br>Their bellowing roars desolated nature, triggered avalanches, and whipped up storms of flame.</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Roar Medallion Effect in Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>Roar Medallion&nbsp;increases the damage of <strong>roar, cry, or shriek skill&nbsp;attacks</strong> by 15%, as well as the unique moves granted to weapons these skills are used with (see notes section below for more details). Note that it does not work on any Breath skills or incantations, despite the description stating the contrary.</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to find Roar Medallion in Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>Dropped by the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Stonedigger Troll" href="/Stonedigger+Troll" target="">Stonedigger Troll</a>, located in the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Limgrave Tunnels" href="/Limgrave+Tunnels" target="">Limgrave Tunnels</a>. He is found at the end of the dungeon. [<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=521&amp;lat=-188.953125&amp;lng=103.090298&amp;zoom=8" href="/Interactive+Map?id=521&amp;lat=-188.953125&amp;lng=103.090298&amp;zoom=8">Map link</a>]</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring&nbsp;Roar Medallion Notes &amp; Tips</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Sell value:&nbsp;<img title="Runes" src="/file/Elden-Ring/runes-currency-elden-ring-wiki-guide-18.png" alt="runes currency elden ring wiki guide 18" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;500</li> 
 <li>Does&nbsp;not work on <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Dragon Communion Incantations" href="/Dragon+Communion+Incantations">Dragon Communion Incantations</a>, <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Placidusax's Ruin" href="/Placidusax's+Ruin">Placidusax' Ruin</a>, <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Aspect of the Crucible: Breath" href="/Aspect+of+the+Crucible:+Breath">Aspect of the Crucible: Breath</a> or <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Firebreather" href="/Firebreather">Firebreather</a>, even though they all involve breathing or roaring both in name and animation.</li> 
 <li>Like stated above, the medallion does not affect breath skills or incantations, even though the description suggests otherwise.</li> 
 <li>Increases the damage of the&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ash of War: Beast's Roar" href="/Ash+of+War:+Beast's+Roar">Beast's Roar</a>,&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Troll's Roar" href="/Troll's+Roar">Troll's Roar</a>&nbsp;and <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Regal Roar" href="/Regal+Roar">Regal Roar</a>&nbsp;projectiles by 15%, as well as the initial gravitational wave of the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Starcaller Cry" href="/Starcaller+Cry">Starcaller Cry</a> skill.</li> 
 <li>Increases the damage of heavy and charged heavy attacks made under the effect of <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring War Cry" href="/War+Cry">War Cry</a>,&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Barbaric Roar" href="/Barbaric+Roar">Barbaric Roar</a>, <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Regal Roar" href="/Regal+Roar">Regal Roar</a> and <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Shriek of Milos" href="/Shriek+of+Milos">Shriek of Milos</a>&nbsp;by 15%, as well as the two-handed heavy attacks and charged heavy attacks made under the effect of <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Braggart's Roar" href="/Braggart's+Roar">Braggart's Roar</a>.&nbsp; 
  <ul> 
   <li>Does not affect heavy jump attacks.</li> 
   <li>Stacks with the passive effect from the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Highland Axe" href="/Highland+Axe">Highland Axe</a>. The Highland Axe will also give its buff to the main-hand weapon while in the off-hand slot when a cry- or roar-type <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War" target="">Ash of War</a> is used with the main-hand weapon, even when two-handing that weapon.</li> 
   <li>Stacks with the buffs from the&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Spiked Cracked Tear" href="/Spiked+Cracked+Tear">Spiked Cracked Tear</a> and <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Axe Talisman" href="/Axe+Talisman">Axe Talisman</a>.</li> 
  </ul> </li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
