				<li id="16493654" class="cmnt-root" data="18" data-d="1646994780000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578460/Roar-Medallion" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">11 Mar 2022 05:33</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16493654" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">The issue with testing the dragon&apos;s breath attacks is that they are multi-hit attacks+ the chance for crits on weak points. it&apos;s hard to tell damage because of that variability. Secondly, the point of testing things like this is to find an answer. don&apos;t be a jerk because someone else got something different from you it&apos;s part of the process. If their wrong let them know, but realize you could be wrong too.<br/><br/>For my test I used the giant west of the Church of Elleh and Ekzykes&apos;s Decay, I timed my attack to hit while the giant stands fully upright for a few seconds after spotting you. This is minimize multi hits.<br/><br/>without the medallion I did exactly 400 dmg<br/>with the medallion it did 400 dmg<br/><br/>I made sure to check the dmg number before scalet rot started dealing dmg<br/><br/>I also noticed that when it critical hitted the giant (the head/eyes of the giant) the attack dealt 401 then immediately after landing 200 more. so that may be the discrepancy some are having with their tests besides the attack multihitting. <br/><br/>Equipment/status:<br/>Dragon Communion seal +5<br/>35 Faith<br/>17 arcane<br/><br/>I&apos;d like to know what everyone else has got testing so feel free to let me know if you&apos;ve got something different in the replies.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16493654" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16493654" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">1</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>20</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>2</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16493654"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16493654" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16493654"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
